Safety and security for this repo:

- NEVER write secrets to mycelium notes. `git notes remove` does not erase old note history.
- Notes in public repos are public data even if GitHub does not render them in the UI.
- Most tooling ignores `refs/notes/*` unless configured. Use gitleaks and explicit notes-aware scans.
- Notes do not travel with normal clone/fetch/push unless `mycelium.sh sync-init` (or equivalent refspec setup) is done.
- Before changing files, read their note context. Before leaving, add or update the notes future agents will depend on.

Treat the invisible layer as durable project memory, not scratch space.
